|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-paleontology/article/new-bothremydid-turtle-testudines-pleurodira-from-the-paleocene-of-northeastern-colombia/7648D30CCCD6BC3A50515E4B7AF31603 |journal=[[Journal of Paleontology]] |volume=86 |pages=688\u2013698 |accessdate=2017-06-14}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=[[Edwin Cadena|Cadena]] |first=Edwin A. |last2=Bloch |first2=Jonathan I. |last3=[[Carlos Jaramillo (geologist)|Jaramillo]] |first3=Carlos A. |year=2010 |title=New Podocnemidid Turtle (Testudines: Pleurodira) from the Middle-Upper Paleocene of South America |url=http://www.bioone.org/doi/abs/10.1080/02724631003621946 |journal=[[Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology]] |volume=30 |pages=367\u2013382 |accessdate=2017-06-14}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Hastings |first=Alexander K. |last2=Bloch |first2=Jonathan I. |last3=[[Carlos Jaramillo (geologist)|Jaramillo]] |first3=Carlos A. |year=2014 |title=A new blunt-snouted dyrosaurid, Anthracosuchus balrogus gen. et sp. nov. (Crocodylomorpha, Mesoeucrocodylia), from the Palaeocene of Colombia |url=http://www.stri.si.edu/sites/publications/PDFs/Hasting_2014_anthracosuchus_Cerrejon.pdf |journal=[[Historical Biology]] |volume=27 |pages=998\u20131020 |accessdate=2017-06-14}}\n* {{cite LSA |last=Herrera |first=Fabiany A. |last2=[[Carlos Jaramillo (geologist)|Jaramillo]] |first2=Carlos A. |last3=Dilcher |first3=David L. |last4=Wing |first4=Scott L. |last5=G\u00f3mez N |first5=Carolina |year=2008 |title=Fossil Araceae from a Paleocene neotropical rainforest in Colombia |url=http://www.amjbot.org/content/95/12/1569 |journal=[[American Journal of Botany]] |volume=95 |pages=1569\u20131583 |accessdate=2017-06-14}}\n\n{{Paleontology in Colombia|state=expanded}}\n{{Portal bar|Geology|Paleontology|Colombia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cerrejon Formation}}\n[[Category:Geologic formations of Colombia]]\n[[Category:Cerrej\u00f3n Formation| ]]\n[[Category:Cesar\u2013Rancher\u00eda Basin|Formations]]\n[[Category:Paleogene Colombia]]\n[[Category:Paleocene Series of South America]]\n[[Category:Itaboraian]]\n[[Category:Peligran]]\n[[Category:Thanetian Stage]]\n[[Category:Coal in Colombia]]\n[[Category:Coal formations]]\n[[Category:Mudstone formations]]\n[[Category:Sandstone formations]]\n[[Category:Siltstone formations]]\n[[Category:Fluvial deposits]]\n[[Category:Reservoir rock formations]]\n[[Category:Source rock formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of Cesar Department|Formations]]\n[[Category:Geography of La Guajira Department|Formations]]\n", "name_user": "IznoRepeat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGeology:replace soft-deprecated editors parameter, gen fixes, misc cite cleaning", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerrej%C3%B3n_Formation"}
{"title_page": "Anne Hegerty", "text_new": "{{short description|Television personality}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Anne Hegerty\n| image              = \n| Spouse             = Jake Hester  \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1958|7|14|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[City of Westminster|Westminster]], [[London]], England\n| occupation         = [[Television personality]]\n| residence          = [[Manchester]], England<ref name=itv1>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/thechase/thechasers/#1|title=The Chase|work=itv.com}}</ref><ref name=Thynne1>{{Cite news |title=The Week in Radio: Why can't the Brain of Britain be a woman? |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/features/the-week-in-radio-why-cant-the-brain-of-britain-be-a-woman-1888693.html |last=Thynne |first=Jane |newspaper=The Independent |date=4 February 2010}}</ref>\n| other_names     =\n \nThe Governess<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/690410/The-Chase-The-Governess-Anne-Hegerty-Dick-Strawbridge-Bradley-Walsh |title=The Chase: Viewers amazed as the Governess makes a shocking confession |first=Neela |last=Debnath |newspaper=Daily Express |date=18 July 2016 |accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref> \n| known_for          = {{nowrap|''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]'' (2010\u2013present)<br/>''[[The Chase Australia]]'' (2015\u2013present)<br/>''[[Britain's Brightest Family]]'' (2018\u2013present)<br/>''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK series 18)|I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]'' (2018)}}\n\n}}\n\n'''Anne Solway Hegerty''' (born 14 July 1958) is an English television quiz [[television personality|personality]] and one of the \"chasers\" on the ITV game show ''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]''. She was a contestant in the 2018 [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] reality show ''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]''.\n\n==Career==\nHegerty is one of the chasers on the ITV game show ''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]'', alongside [[Mark Labbett]], [[Shaun Wallace]], [[Paul Sinha]] and [[Jenny Ryan]]. As well as being in the UK version, she is also a chaser on the [[The Chase Australia|Australian version of the show]] on the [[Seven Network]] with fellow UK chasers Mark Labbett and Shaun Wallace.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Knox |first1=David |title=Secrets of Anne Hegerty's success |url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2017/05/secrets-of-anne-hegertys-success.html |accessdate=18 December 2018 |publisher=[[TV Tonight]] |date=22 May 2017}}</ref> In the ''Chase'' episode aired on 15 April 2019, Hegerty went through the whole show without getting an answer wrong.<ref>https://mobile.twitter.com/MarkLabbett/status/1117847621152886784</ref><ref>http://www.onequestionshootout.xyz/stats/overall.htm</ref>\n\nHegerty has made appearances on a number of other quiz shows, including ''[[Mastermind (TV series)|Mastermind]]'', ''[[Fifteen to One]]'', ''[[Today's the Day (game show)|Today's the Day]]'', ''[[Are You an Egghead?]]'' and ''[[Brain of Britain]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bradleywalsh.co.uk/tv-the-chase-meet-the-chasers.php |title=''The Chase'': Meet the Chasers |publisher=[[Bradley Walsh]]}}</ref> {{As of|2016|10|post=,}} she was ranked 55th (and second among women) in the World Quizzing Championships.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldquizzing.com/results/ |title=Results |work=worldquizzing.com |access-date=13 June 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120607192638/http://www.worldquizzing.com/results/ |archive-date=7 June 2012 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> In November 2013 she competed in the Bolton Premier Quiz League to become Brain of Bolton for the second time.<ref name=\"Brain of Bolton\">{{cite news |title=TV quiz champion named Brain of Bolton for second time |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10791790.TV_quiz_champion_named_Brain_of_Bolton_for_second_time/ |last=Scoble |first=Andy |newspaper=The Bolton News |date=7 November 2013|accessdate=14 April 2014}}</ref> \n\nHegarty appeared as the \"phone a friend\" for a competitor, Lisa Harman from Ecclesfield, on ''[[Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? (British game show)|Who Wants to be A Millionaire]]'' in 2010; Harman won \u00a375,000. Hegerty correctly answered the question about the author of ''[[Twilight (novel series)|Twilight]]''.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=anne_hegerty|number=949534227187499008|date=5 June 2019|title=Yes, everybody, that was me...}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014, Hegerty appeared in the [[pantomime]] ''[[Cinderella]]'' as the wicked stepmother at the Grange Theatre in [[Northwich]].<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite news |url=http://www.independentnewspapers.co.uk/midcheshire/viewstory/4175/WIN-TICKETS-TO-CINDERELLA.html#.VL64wVV1-uY |title=Win tickets to Cinderella |work=Mid-Cheshire Independent |publisher=Independent Newspapers |date=6 November 2014 |accessdate=20 January 2015 }}</ref> In December 2015 she appeared as Fleshcreep in the pantomime ''[[Jack and the Beanstalk]]'' at the Civic Hall, [[Ellesmere Port]],<ref name=\"Cheshire Chronicle\">{{cite news |url=http://www.chesterchronicle.co.uk/news/chester-cheshire-news/ellesmere-port-dancers-star-annual-10681605 |title=Ellesmere Port Dancers Star in Annual Panto |work=Chester Chronicle |date=4 January 2016 |accessdate=5 February 2016 }}</ref> which was also booked for performance at Heywood and Radcliffe. At Easter 2016, Hegerty appeared as the Enchantress in the pantomime ''[[Beauty and the Beast]]'', alongside [[Keith Chegwin]] and [[Basil Brush]], at the [[Palace Theatre, Redditch|Palace Theatre]], [[Redditch]], which sold out, and other venues.<ref name=\"Redditch and Alcester Advertiser\">{{cite news |url=http://www.redditchadvertiser.co.uk/news/14373796.Beauty_and_The_Beast_at_Redditch_s_Palace_Theatre/ |title=Beauty and the Beast at Redditch's Palace Theatre |work=Redditch and Alcester Advertiser |date=21 March 2016 |accessdate=9 April 2016 }}</ref> From 6 December 2016 to 1 January 2017, she appeared as Blackweed in the pantomime ''[[Jack and the Beanstalk]]'' at the [[Kings Theatre, Southsea|Kings Theatre]], [[Southsea]], [[Portsmouth]].<ref name=\"The News\">{{cite news |url=http://www.portsmouth.co.uk/whats-on/theatre/cast-climb-to-the-stars-in-the-kings-panto-jack-and-the-beanstalk-1-7612408/ |title=Cast climb to the stars in The Kings panto, Jack and the Beanstalk |work=The News |date=4 October 2016 |accessdate=16 December 2016 }}</ref> From 8 to 31 December 2017, she appeared as The Empress of China in the pantomime ''[[Aladdin]]'' at the [[Princess Theatre, Torquay|Princess Theatre (Torquay)]].<ref name=\"By The Dart\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bythedart.co.uk/events/aladdin-torquay// |title=Aladdin Pantomime |work=By The Dart |accessdate=3 January 2018 }}{{Dead link|date=December 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> From 18 December 2018 to 6 January 2019, she appeared as Queen Rat in the pantomime ''[[Dick Whittington]]'' at the [[Theatre Royal, Windsor|Theatre Royal (Windsor)]]; Anita Harris played the role until Hegerty returned from ''I'm a Celebrity ... Get Me Out of Here''.<ref name=\"What's On\">{{cite news |url=http://www.theatreroyalwindsor.co.uk/details.php?id=658// |title=Dick Whittington |work=Theatre Royal, Windsor |accessdate=6 January 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"Dick Whittington at Theatre Royal, Windsor\">{{cite news |url=https://www.maidenhead-advertiser.co.uk/news/christmas/138989/review-dick-whittington-at-theatre-royal-windsor.html// |title=Dick Whittington |work=Maidenhead Advertiser |accessdate=6 January 2018 }}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> From 5 December 2019 to 5 January 2020, she appeared as Carabosse in the pantomime ''[[Sleeping Beauty]]'' at [[Middlesbrough Theatre]].<ref name=\"The Northern Echo\">{{cite news |url=https://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/news/local/teesvalley/17939563.itvs-anne-hegerty-chasing-panto-dream-sleeping-beauty// |title=ITV's Anne Hegerty chasing the panto dream in Sleeping Beauty|work=The Northern Echo |date=2 October 2019 |accessdate=11 January 2020 }}</ref>\n\nOn 19 October 2017, Hegerty appeared alongside fellow chaser Mark Labbett on an episode of ''[[Celebrity Juice]]''. She also guested on an edition of BBC Radio 4's ''[[I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue]]'', which was broadcast in December 2017. \n\nSince January 2018, Hegerty has presented ''[[Britain's Brightest Family]]'' on [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/presscentre/ep1week1/britains-brightest-family|title=Britain&#039;s Brightest Family Episode 1|work=\"ITV Press Centre\"|access-date=3 December 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171204222831/http://www.itv.com/presscentre/ep1week1/britains-brightest-family|archive-date=4 December 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHegerty came in 75th place in the [[World Quizzing Championship|World Quizzing Championship of 2018]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldquizzingchampionships.com/results/|title=Results \u2013 World Quizzing Championships|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 November 2018, she participated in that year's series of ''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK series 18)|I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]'', where she finished 7th.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/12/05/anne-hegerty-fifth-celebrity-booted-im-celebrity-jungle-8213826/|title=Anne Hegerty is the fifth celebrity booted out of I'm A Celebrity jungle|last=Deen|first=Sarah|date=2018-12-05|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2018-12-05}}</ref><ref name=\"argus\">{{cite news |url=https://www.southwalesargus.co.uk/news/17221184.former-argus-journalist-anne-hegerty-to-appear-in-im-a-celebrity-get-me-out-of-here/ |first=Tomos |last=Povey |title=Former Argus journalist Anne Hegerty to appear in I'm a Celebrity... Get Me Out Of Here! |newspaper=South Wales Argus |date=13 November 2018 |accessdate=10 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, she joined 26 other celebrities at [[Metropolis Group|Metropolis Studios]] and performed an original Christmas song called Rock With Rudolph. The song was recorded in aid of Great Ormond Street Hospital and was released digitally through independent record label Saga Entertainment on the 30th November 2018. The music video debuted exclusively with [[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]] on 29 November 2018 and had its first TV showing on [[Good Morning Britain (2014 TV programme)|Good Morning Britain]] on 30 November 2018. The song peaked at number two on the iTunes pop chart.<ref>https://www.itv.com/news/london/2018-11-30/tv-stars-sing-for-great-ormond-street-christmas-charity-single/</ref><ref>https://www.femalefirst.co.uk/music/interviews/gail-porter-interview-great-ormond-street-hospital-christmas-charity-single-rock-with-rudolph-1174732.html</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHegerty started her journalistic career in the 1980s as a reporter and feature writer at the ''[[South Wales Argus]]'', based in Newport, South Wales, before moving to Manchester, England.<ref name=\"argus\" /> Hegerty has also worked as a ghostwriter.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=anne_hegerty|number=1136248587019440128|date=5 June 2019|title=I actually once wrote two books under the name Richard Scarry.  (With his permission, I should add.  He couldn't do EVERYTHING himself.)  They were a bit rubbish and nobody bought them.}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#b0c4de; text-align:center;\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Channel\n|- \n| 1988\n| ''[[Mastermind (TV series)|Mastermind]]'' \n| Contestant \n| [[BBC]]\n|-\n| 2010\u2013present\n| ''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]''\n| rowspan=2|Chaser \n| [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]\n|-\n| 2015\u2013present\n| ''[[The Chase Australia]]''\n| [[Seven Network|Channel 7]]\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present\n| ''[[Britain's Brightest Family]]''\n| Presenter\n| rowspan=2|[[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK TV series)|I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]''\n|Contestant\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=6712765|name=Anne Hegerty}}\n\n{{The Chase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hegerty, Anne}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Quiz championship players]]\n[[Category:Contestants on British game shows]]\n[[Category:English television personalities]]\n[[Category:English Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Writers from London]]\n[[Category:People from the City of Westminster]]\n[[Category:People with Asperger syndrome]]\n[[Category:People from Wood Green]]\n[[Category:Participants in British reality television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Television personality}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Anne Hegerty\n| image              = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1958|7|14|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[City of Westminster|Westminster]], [[London]], England\n| occupation         = [[Television personality]]\n| residence          = [[Manchester]], England<ref name=itv1>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/thechase/thechasers/#1|title=The Chase|work=itv.com}}</ref><ref name=Thynne1>{{Cite news |title=The Week in Radio: Why can't the Brain of Britain be a woman? |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/features/the-week-in-radio-why-cant-the-brain-of-britain-be-a-woman-1888693.html |last=Thynne |first=Jane |newspaper=The Independent |date=4 February 2010}}</ref>\n| other_names     =\n \nThe Governess<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/690410/The-Chase-The-Governess-Anne-Hegerty-Dick-Strawbridge-Bradley-Walsh |title=The Chase: Viewers amazed as the Governess makes a shocking confession |first=Neela |last=Debnath |newspaper=Daily Express |date=18 July 2016 |accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref> \n| known_for          = {{nowrap|''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]'' (2010\u2013present)<br/>''[[The Chase Australia]]'' (2015\u2013present)<br/>''[[Britain's Brightest Family]]'' (2018\u2013present)<br/>''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK series 18)|I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]'' (2018)}}\n\n}}\n\n'''Anne Solway Hegerty''' (born 14 July 1958) is an English television quiz [[television personality|personality]] and one of the \"chasers\" on the ITV game show ''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]''. She was a contestant in the 2018 [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] reality show ''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]''.\n\n==Career==\nHegerty is one of the chasers on the ITV game show ''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]'', alongside [[Mark Labbett]], [[Shaun Wallace]], [[Paul Sinha]] and [[Jenny Ryan]]. As well as being in the UK version, she is also a chaser on the [[The Chase Australia|Australian version of the show]] on the [[Seven Network]] with fellow UK chasers Mark Labbett and Shaun Wallace.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Knox |first1=David |title=Secrets of Anne Hegerty's success |url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2017/05/secrets-of-anne-hegertys-success.html |accessdate=18 December 2018 |publisher=[[TV Tonight]] |date=22 May 2017}}</ref> In the ''Chase'' episode aired on 15 April 2019, Hegerty went through the whole show without getting an answer wrong.<ref>https://mobile.twitter.com/MarkLabbett/status/1117847621152886784</ref><ref>http://www.onequestionshootout.xyz/stats/overall.htm</ref>\n\nHegerty has made appearances on a number of other quiz shows, including ''[[Mastermind (TV series)|Mastermind]]'', ''[[Fifteen to One]]'', ''[[Today's the Day (game show)|Today's the Day]]'', ''[[Are You an Egghead?]]'' and ''[[Brain of Britain]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bradleywalsh.co.uk/tv-the-chase-meet-the-chasers.php |title=''The Chase'': Meet the Chasers |publisher=[[Bradley Walsh]]}}</ref> {{As of|2016|10|post=,}} she was ranked 55th (and second among women) in the World Quizzing Championships.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldquizzing.com/results/ |title=Results |work=worldquizzing.com |access-date=13 June 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120607192638/http://www.worldquizzing.com/results/ |archive-date=7 June 2012 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> In November 2013 she competed in the Bolton Premier Quiz League to become Brain of Bolton for the second time.<ref name=\"Brain of Bolton\">{{cite news |title=TV quiz champion named Brain of Bolton for second time |url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/news/10791790.TV_quiz_champion_named_Brain_of_Bolton_for_second_time/ |last=Scoble |first=Andy |newspaper=The Bolton News |date=7 November 2013|accessdate=14 April 2014}}</ref> \n\nHegarty appeared as the \"phone a friend\" for a competitor, Lisa Harman from Ecclesfield, on ''[[Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? (British game show)|Who Wants to be A Millionaire]]'' in 2010; Harman won \u00a375,000. Hegerty correctly answered the question about the author of ''[[Twilight (novel series)|Twilight]]''.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=anne_hegerty|number=949534227187499008|date=5 June 2019|title=Yes, everybody, that was me...}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014, Hegerty appeared in the [[pantomime]] ''[[Cinderella]]'' as the wicked stepmother at the Grange Theatre in [[Northwich]].<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite news |url=http://www.independentnewspapers.co.uk/midcheshire/viewstory/4175/WIN-TICKETS-TO-CINDERELLA.html#.VL64wVV1-uY |title=Win tickets to Cinderella |work=Mid-Cheshire Independent |publisher=Independent Newspapers |date=6 November 2014 |accessdate=20 January 2015 }}</ref> In December 2015 she appeared as Fleshcreep in the pantomime ''[[Jack and the Beanstalk]]'' at the Civic Hall, [[Ellesmere Port]],<ref name=\"Cheshire Chronicle\">{{cite news |url=http://www.chesterchronicle.co.uk/news/chester-cheshire-news/ellesmere-port-dancers-star-annual-10681605 |title=Ellesmere Port Dancers Star in Annual Panto |work=Chester Chronicle |date=4 January 2016 |accessdate=5 February 2016 }}</ref> which was also booked for performance at Heywood and Radcliffe. At Easter 2016, Hegerty appeared as the Enchantress in the pantomime ''[[Beauty and the Beast]]'', alongside [[Keith Chegwin]] and [[Basil Brush]], at the [[Palace Theatre, Redditch|Palace Theatre]], [[Redditch]], which sold out, and other venues.<ref name=\"Redditch and Alcester Advertiser\">{{cite news |url=http://www.redditchadvertiser.co.uk/news/14373796.Beauty_and_The_Beast_at_Redditch_s_Palace_Theatre/ |title=Beauty and the Beast at Redditch's Palace Theatre |work=Redditch and Alcester Advertiser |date=21 March 2016 |accessdate=9 April 2016 }}</ref> From 6 December 2016 to 1 January 2017, she appeared as Blackweed in the pantomime ''[[Jack and the Beanstalk]]'' at the [[Kings Theatre, Southsea|Kings Theatre]], [[Southsea]], [[Portsmouth]].<ref name=\"The News\">{{cite news |url=http://www.portsmouth.co.uk/whats-on/theatre/cast-climb-to-the-stars-in-the-kings-panto-jack-and-the-beanstalk-1-7612408/ |title=Cast climb to the stars in The Kings panto, Jack and the Beanstalk |work=The News |date=4 October 2016 |accessdate=16 December 2016 }}</ref> From 8 to 31 December 2017, she appeared as The Empress of China in the pantomime ''[[Aladdin]]'' at the [[Princess Theatre, Torquay|Princess Theatre (Torquay)]].<ref name=\"By The Dart\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bythedart.co.uk/events/aladdin-torquay// |title=Aladdin Pantomime |work=By The Dart |accessdate=3 January 2018 }}{{Dead link|date=December 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> From 18 December 2018 to 6 January 2019, she appeared as Queen Rat in the pantomime ''[[Dick Whittington]]'' at the [[Theatre Royal, Windsor|Theatre Royal (Windsor)]]; Anita Harris played the role until Hegerty returned from ''I'm a Celebrity ... Get Me Out of Here''.<ref name=\"What's On\">{{cite news |url=http://www.theatreroyalwindsor.co.uk/details.php?id=658// |title=Dick Whittington |work=Theatre Royal, Windsor |accessdate=6 January 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"Dick Whi